headline: C.H. Robinson price target raised to $124 from $115 at Baird
summary: Baird raised the firm’s price target on C.H. Robinson (CHRW) to $124 from $115 and keeps a Neutral rating on the shares. The firm said its investor day included credible plans to increase market share, sustain productivity/efficiency gains, and navigate a cyclical freight market inflection. Baird said its execution encouraging and they would get more constructive on pullbacks. Published first on TheFly – the ultimate source for real-time, market-moving breaking financial news.
